"/>，僅有利於中華民國統治的[[台灣抗日運動|抗日運動]]才能被強調，且加強台灣屬於中國的觀念，鞏固統治基礎<ref>[https://sites.google.com/site/yanxian1947/lun-wen/guojiajiangouyurizhitaiwanshiyanjiu 四、台灣觀點的建立] {{Wayback|url=https://sites.google.com/site/yanxian1947/lun-wen/guojiajiangouyurizhitaiwanshiyanjiu |date=20210125033411 }}，殖民化與近代化—檢視日治時代的台灣，張炎憲，2007-09-08</ref>。台灣學生接受了以中國為主體的史觀教育，以便使一黨專政的獨裁統治合理化<ref>{{cite book | author = Kristina Jonsson; Catarina Kinnvall | title = Globalization and Democratization in Asia: The Construction of Identity | url = https://books.google.com.tw/books?id=Qo_KvEMtmj4C&printsec=frontcover&hl=zh-TW&pg=PA65#v=onepage&q&f=false | publisher = [[Routledge|Routledge]] | location = [[London|London]] | date = 2003 | isbn = 1134473249 | page = 65 | quote = Since the arrival of Chiang Kai-shek's Nationalist Party on Taiwan at the end of the 1940s, island students were taught to be proud of mainland China's 5,000-year history. This historical identity was meant to legitimate power for Chinag's dictatorial party. | access-date = 2017-07-22 | archive-date = 2021-01-25 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210125033422/https://books.google.com.tw/books?id=Qo_KvEMtmj4C&printsec=frontcover&hl=zh-TW&pg=PA65#v=onepage&q&f=false | dead-url = no }}</ref>。[[小學|小學]]教育也受到了中國國民黨当局的影響<ref>{{cite book | author = [[布魯斯·卡明斯|布魯斯·卡明斯]] | title = Parallax Visions: Making Sense of American-East Asian Relations | url = https://books.google.com.tw/books?id=oKfb-RZaB_EC&printsec=frontcover&pg=PA89&hl=zh-TW#v=onepage&q&f=false | publisher = {{link-en|杜克大學出版社|Duke University Press|Duke University Press}} | location = [[德罕_(北卡羅來納州)|德罕]] | date = 2002 | isbn = 0822329247 | page = 89 | quote = d. Postwar North Korea and Taiwan: universal elementary school education, with practices modified by Soviet and Kuomintang influences; | access-date = 2017-07-22 | archive-date = 2021-01-25 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210125033418/https://books.google.com.tw/books?id=oKfb-RZaB_EC&printsec=frontcover&pg=PA89&hl=zh-TW#v=onepage&q&f=false | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

