…稱之為白色恐怖，這個時期人民許多言論自由都被限制，也很容易因為批評當時政府而被抓去約談入獄。}}</ref><ref>[http://enews.url.com.tw/enews/26586 媽媽流淚的時代] {{Wayback|url=http://enews.url.com.tw/enews/26586 |date=20210125033532 }}，黃崇松，智邦生活館，2004-04-23</ref>，異議人士甚至會被送到[[綠島|綠島]]的[[集中營|集中營]]進行酷刑折磨和思想改造<ref>{{cite book | author = Dafydd Fell | title = Government and Politics in Taiwan | url = https://books.google.com.tw/books?id=uO3FBQAAQBAJ&pg=PT61&lpg=PT61&dq=corporatism,%20brainwashing&source=bl&ots=Jfyr8hGEIM&sig=jRgin_FQW06ar2YjdsClH3cvqMc&hl=zh-TW&sa=X&ved=corporatism,%20brainwashing#v=onepage&q=corporatism%2C%20brainwashing&f=false | publisher = [[Routledge|Routledge]] | location = [[London|London]] | date = 2012 | isbn = 1136617736 | quote = Where corporatism, brainwashing, material improvement and clientelism failed to work, the KMT employed severe political repression. | access-date = 2017-07-22 | archive-date = 2019-05-13 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190513182112/https://books.google.com.tw/books?id=uO3FBQAAQBAJ&pg=PT61&lpg=PT61&dq=corporatism,%20brainwashing&source=bl&ots=Jfyr8hGEIM&sig=jRgin_FQW06ar2YjdsClH3cvqMc&hl=zh-TW&sa=X&ved=corporatism,%20brainwashing#v=onepage&q=corporatism%2C%20brainwashing&f=false | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{cite book | author = David Curtis Wright | title = The History of China | url = https://books.google.com.tw/books?id=jTD6V3bKixwC&printsec=frontcover&pg=PA251&hl=zh-TW#v=onepage&q&f=false | publisher = {{link-en|ABC-CLIO}} | location = [[Santa_Barbara,_California|Santa Barbara, California]] | date = 2011 | isbn = 0313377480 | page = 251 | quote = Many of the most prominent dissidents were eventually imprisoned for years on Green Island (about 30 kilometers east of Taiwan) in an infamous brainwashing and torture concentration camp run by the Kuomintang. | access-date = 2017-07-22 | archive-date = 2021-01-25 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210125033450/https://books.google.com.tw/books?id=jTD6V3bKixwC&printsec=frontcover&pg=PA251&hl=zh-TW#v=onepage&q&f=false | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

